This paper is about neural machine translation (NMT), which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the computer science category. The paper specifically focuses on Chinese-English NMT and explores the most suitable translation granularity for this language pair. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with NLP and related topics. Other likely sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.IR (Information Retrieval), as these sub-categories also cover topics related to NMT and machine learning.
